    <h1>The Science of the Void</h1>
    <p>How do we calculate neighborhood vibrancy? It’s not a guess—it’s data. We measure the "Insulation Index" of a zip code using three primary cultural sensors.</p>
    
    <div class="metric-grid">
        <div class="metric-card">
            <h3>1. Acoustic Permeability</h3>
            <p>We measure the distance a 100Hz bass frequency travels before hitting a "Noise Complaint" trigger. Low permeability indicates "The Void."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
            <h3>2. The Spice Constant</h3>
            <p>A calculation of the density of non-franchise restaurants. If the only available seasoning is 'Black Pepper,' the index drops by 40%.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
            <h3>3. Beige Saturation</h3>
            <p>Using satellite imagery, we scan for architectural monotony. High concentrations of 'Eggshell' and 'Desert Sand' paint indicate social stagnation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
            <h3>4. The Shush Factor</h3>
            <p>A real-time tracking of neighborhood forum keywords. High frequencies of "Is it just me or is it loud?" signal a Critical Void event.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
